  "text": "It thus remains to show the same for the odd subspaces. We note that if ψ ∈ L − (Γ 1 ) then [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] imply that ψ(x) = 0 for all points x which are not on the leaves of Γ 1 and similarly for Γ 2 . Therefore, ψ ∈ L − (Γ 1 ) is an eigenfunction of Γ 1 with eigenvalue λ if and only if it is an eigenfunction of Γ 2 with the same eigenvalue and so σ − (Γ 1 ) = σ − (Γ 2 ). The same reasoning implies that σ − (Γ 1 ) = σ − (Γ 2 ), which completes the result.",
